  Phase 8 — Insights (AI)

  Go to /insights (as MANAGER).

  Test 8.1 — Period toggle
  - Today / This Week / This Month → stat cards and charts update

  Test 8.2 — Charts
  - Hourly Orders: bar chart (9AM–9PM), bars where orders exist
  - Revenue This Week: area chart with gradient fill for last 7 days
  - Top Items: horizontal CSS bars showing top items by order count

  Test 8.3 — Key Metrics cards
  - Avg Order Value: computed from filtered orders
  - Total Revenue: sum of filtered order amounts (Rs.)
  - Customer Satisfaction: avg rating / 5
  - Kitchen Efficiency: 100% − cancelled%

  Test 8.4 — AI Insights (requires FastAPI running)
  - Click "Generate Insights" button
  - Should call POST /api/ai/insights
  - Insight text appears in amber-bordered card
  - Test error state: stop FastAPI (Ctrl+C in terminal 3), click Generate → inline error shows

  ---
  Phase 9 — Real-Time WebSocket Stress Test

  Open 3 browser windows simultaneously:
  1. Window A: /dashboard (MANAGER)
  2. Window B: /orders (MANAGER)
  3. Window C: /kitchen (KITCHEN user)

  Test 9.1 — New order propagation
  curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/orders \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer $CUST_TOKEN" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -d "{\"tableId\":\"$TABLE_ID\",\"items\":[{\"menuItemId\":\"$ITEM_ID\",\"quantity\":1}]}"
  - All 3 windows should update within ~1 second (no refresh needed)

  Test 9.2 — Status change propagation
  - In Window B, click "Confirm" on the new order
  - Window A dashboard live orders panel updates
  - Window C kitchen display shows the confirmed order

  Test 9.3 — WebSocket reconnect
  - Temporarily stop Spring Boot (Ctrl+C), wait 10 seconds, restart it
  - The frontend should auto-reconnect (STOMP reconnectDelay: 5000) and show live data again

  ---
  Phase 10 — Role-Based Access

  Test 10.1 — WAITER restrictions
  - Login as waiter@test.com
  - Can access: /dashboard, /orders, /tables
  - Menu page: can view but CANNOT add/edit/delete items or categories (buttons should be hidden or API returns 403)

  Test 10.2 — API-level auth (Postman/curl)
  # Try to create menu item as WAITER — should get 403
  WAITER_TOKEN=$(curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -d '{"email":"waiter@test.com","password":"pass123"}' | python3 -c "import sys,json; print(json.load(sys.stdin)['token'])")

  curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/menu/categories \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer $WAITER_TOKEN" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -d '{"name":"Test"}'
  # Expected: 403 Forbidden

  # Try to access reviews as WAITER — should get 403
  curl -H "Authorization: Bearer $WAITER_TOKEN" http://localhost:8080/api/reviews
  # Expected: 403 Forbidden

  # Try to place order as MANAGER — should get 403
  curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/orders \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -d "{\"tableId\":\"$TABLE_ID\",\"items\":[{\"menuItemId\":\"$ITEM_ID\",\"quantity\":1}]}"
  # Expected: 403 Forbidden (only CUSTOMER can place orders)

